Stay at home
Only go outside for food, health reasons or work (but only if you cannot work from home)
If you go out, stay 2 metres (6ft) away from other people at all times
Wash your hands as soon as you get home
Do not meet others, even friends or family.
You can spread the virus even if you don’t have symptoms.

Cases of coronavirus (COVID 19) have been confirmed in Grenada. Government announced a limited State of Emergency for 21 days from 25 March with a curfew and Emergency Powers regulations to limit the spread of the virus.
The Ministry of Health Grenada is asking the public to call the COVID-19 enquiries information line on 538 4787 or 458 4787 if they have any symptoms such as cough fever or difficulty breathing, and visit the Government’s webpage for the latest information on the virus.
With the announcement of the airport closure from 23 March, incoming passengers are no longer allowed to enter Grenada. From 16 March, disembarkation from cruise vessels will also not be permitted in Grenada. Effective 22 March, non-Grenadian passengers and crew on yachts will not be permitted to disembark in Grenada, Carriacou, and Petite Martinique. Any failure to comply will result in a fine or detention.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
